name: Xaa-Pro aminopeptidase
reaction: Release of any N-terminal amino acid, including proline, that is linked to proline, even from a dipeptide or tripeptide
comment: A Mn2+-dependent, generally membrane-bound enzyme present in both mammalian and bacterial cells. In peptidase family M24 (methionyl aminopeptidase family)
